Title: Finally! Azure Service Bus Emulator is Now Available!
Description:
Are you building a scalable, decoupled application together with a service bus? 

If you're using Azure Service Bus, you've probably felt the pain of local development!

Up until now, there hasn't been a way to work with Azure Service Bus without setting that up in Azure, which costs money, and requires you to always be online. 

Let me introduce the Azure Service Bus Emulator that solves this problem. You can now run the emulator in docker, locally, and point your application to the local instance. This will let you build an application that uses Azure Service Bus without relying on Azure during the development process!

Join me in this video where we explore this new tool, and set it up using .NET Aspire!

Title: Insane performance boost in EF core using bulk operations #dotnet #aspnetcore #csharp #efcore
Description: In this video, I dive into the insane performance boost you can achieve in .NET  by leveraging bulk operations with ExecuteUpdateAsync and ExecuteDeleteAsync from EF Core. I demonstrate two approaches for updating and deleting records: the traditional method that loads entities into memory and processes them using foreach loops, and the optimized bulk operation method. The difference? 6 seconds vs. 0.1 seconds!

RFC 35140: The Do-Not-Stab flag in the HTTP Header
Description:
Date: March 7, 2111
Abstract
This document defines the syntax and semantics of the Do-Not-Stab header, a proposed HTTP header
that allows users to indicate to a website their preferences about being stabbed. It also provides
a standard for how services should comply with such user preferences, if they wish to.
